The paper discusses the use of machine learning for medical image analysis, specifically for exam triage. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of non-image features in the dataset also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the potential application of this technology in healthcare settings suggests the involvement of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
